Edit existing controlled vocabulary

 

â€ŒThere ability to edit a controlled vocabulary when it is opened for preview. The administrator is able to edit both the the details of an existing controlled vocabulary and its values.

  • The user opens the controlled vocabulary (1).
  • When "Edit details and values" (2) on a controlled vocabulary is selected:

 

  • Then the a controlled vocabulary is opened in edit mode.
    • The user could edit both the a controlled vocabulary details (1,2) ( name, comment in different languages and the values (3) ( names, comments, change extras, etc.)
  • When "Save changes"(4) is selected, all the changes made on the a controlled vocabulary are saved.

 

Create new controlled vocabulary

 

The administrator is able to create a new controlled vocabulary in the system.

  • The administrator selects Administration menu/ Controlled vocabularies. There is action Add controlled vocabulary (1) at the top of the list with controlled vocabularies.
  • When the action is selected then Create new vocabulary form is displayed.
  • The user has to fill in the following data for a new vocabulary:
    • Identifier (2) - unique ID of the vocabulary. The field is mandatory. Two vocabularies with the same identifier could not exist.
    • Name (3) - the name in the default system language. The field is mandatory .
    • All other properties of a vocabulary like  - Comment in default language, name and comment in other system languages, extras (4) are optional an the user could enter them or not.
  • Empty vocabulary with only unique ID (controlled vocabulary without any value) could be created.
  • When Create vocabulary (5) is selected, then the new vocabulary is created.
  • The new vocabulary is displayed in the list, sorted based on its identifier.

 

Add new values in existing controlled vocabulary

 The administrator is able to add new values in an existing controlled vocabulary, could be both imported from excel or created in SEP.

  • For each controlled vocabulary in edit mode, there is action Add value (1).
  • When the action is selected, then Create new value form is opened.
  • For each new value the user should enter the following data:
    • Identifier (2) - unique ID of the value in the current vocabulary. The field is mandatory. There could be values with the same code but in different controlled vocabularies.
    • Name (3) - the name of the value in the default system language. The field is mandatory and unique for the current vocabulary.
    • All other properties of a value, like: Comment in default language, name and comment in other system languages, extras are optional an the user could enter them or not.
  • When action Save changes (5) is selected then the new value is added in the controlled vocabulary.
    • The values in the vocabulary are sorted alphabetically based on Identifiers of the values, and the new value is displayed in the list of values based on its identifier.
    • The new value is created as Active.

 

Activate/ Deactivate values from an existing controlled vocabulary

 The administrator is able to deactivate values from a controlled vocabulary in case not to use these values anymore. The actions activate/ deactivate are performed in Edit mode of the vocabulary.

  • When the checkbox of a code value with status Active is selected (1), then the status of the value changes to Inactive.
    • Inactive values could not be selected when a new item is created, that uses the respective vocabulary.
  • When the checkbox of a code value with status Inactive is selected (2) the status of the code value changes to Active and it could be used both for creation of new objects and search.
